    "While varying the layer thickness we observe that thin layers increase local stress contrasts and produce strong oscillations in σ₁ and σ₃, whereas thicker layers smooth these variations and make the system behave more like a uniform medium. As a result, differential stress becomes increasingly controlled by bulk density and Poisson’s ratio as layer thickness increases.\n",
    "\n",
