    "\n",
    "##### *Task 4 (Bonus Part): Making a stress concentration plot aroundthe fracture tip.*\n",
    "\n",
    "A stress concentration plot around a fracture tip was generated as a reference for future finite element model (FEM) validation. The analysis is based on Mode I linear elastic fracture mechanics (LEFM), with far-field loading from Part 2 Task 1:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sigma_0 = \\sigma_h = 26\\ \\text{MPa}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "For pure opening mode ($K_{II}=0$), the near-tip stresses are:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sigma_r = \\frac{K_I}{\\sqrt{2\\pi r}} \\cos\\frac{\\theta}{2} \\left(1 + \\sin^2\\frac{\\theta}{2}\\right)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sigma_\\theta = \\frac{K_I}{\\sqrt{2\\pi r}} \\cos\\frac{\\theta}{2} \\cos^2\\frac{\\theta}{2}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\tau_{r\\theta} = \\frac{K_I}{\\sqrt{2\\pi r}} \\cos\\frac{\\theta}{2} \\sin\\theta\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "with\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "K_I = \\sigma_0\\sqrt{\\pi a}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The opening stress used for interpretation is the Cartesian component $\\sigma_y$ after transforming from polar to Cartesian coordinates."
